cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

The paper focuses on vehicle Re-ID, which is a computer vision task, and proposes a deep learning model to extract features from both global and local regions. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a novel learning algorithm to jointly use multiple cues for training, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with large-scale datasets, which may fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of deep learning models and the focus on feature extraction and learning may also suggest cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the problem of distinguishing between similar vehicles, which may involve security and privacy concerns, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a possible sub-category as well.
